import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['precipitation'] = pd.to_numeric(data['precipitation'], errors='coerce')
    sns.boxplot(x='location', y='precipitation', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation across different locations?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date'])
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_max', data=data, label='Maximum Temperature')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_min', data=data, label='Minimum Temperature')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.title('How does the temperature vary over time?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date'])
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data['day'] = data['date'].dt.day
    data['weekday'] = data['date'].dt.weekday
    data['weather'] = data['weather'].str.title()
    data = data.groupby(['weather'])['count'].sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by=['count'], ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x="weather", y="count", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='Weather Condition', ylabel='Count')
    ax.axhline(y=data['count'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['count'].max()))
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
